            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Most companies need 2-4 personas. Early-stage startups with one product often need 2. Enterprises with multiple product lines may need 4-5. More than 5 usually means personas that are too narrow to be useful.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">How do you research a buyer persona?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Interview 5-10 existing customers plus 2-3 lost prospects, mine your CRM for firmographic patterns, analyse Google Analytics behaviour, survey your email list, and sit in on sales calls. Personas built without interviews are guesses.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">Are buyer personas still relevant in 2026?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Yes — but only as living documents refreshed with real data. Static, decorative personas built once and filed away add no value. Personas that inform targeting, messaging, and content strategy still drive measurable revenue lift.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the difference between a buyer persona and an ICP?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>A buyer persona describes an individual — their goals, pain points, and behaviour. An ICP describes an account or company — industry, size, tech stack, revenue. Personas power messaging; ICPs power targeting.</p></div></div>
          </div>
          <div class="faq-item">
            <button class="faq-q" onclick="toggleFaq(this)"><span class="faq-q-text">What is the biggest buyer persona mistake?</span><span class="faq-toggle"><svg viewBox="0 0 12 12"><path d="M6 1v10M1 6h10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"/></svg></span></button>
            <div class="faq-a"><div class="faq-a-inner"><p>Building personas from assumptions rather than customer interviews. Second most common: creating too many personas — five or more — so no one on the team remembers them or writes for them.</p></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>

